Package Model

Class Reports

  • java.lang.Object
    • Model.Reports
  • public class Reports
extends java.lang.Object
    The Reports class is a model class. This class is similar to the appointments class but with slightly different parameters. The Reports class is used to display specific information regarding appointments.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Reports

        public Reports​(java.time.Month month,
               java.lang.String type,
               int count)
        This is the first constructor for the Reports class. This method is used for the type and month reporting.
        Parameters:
        type - name of the type of appointment
        month - month the appointment takes place
        count - number of appointments with the same month and type

      • Reports

        public Reports​(int appointmentID,
               java.lang.String title,
               java.lang.String description,
               java.lang.String location,
               java.lang.String type,
               java.sql.Timestamp start,
               java.sql.Timestamp end,
               int customerID,
               int contactID)
        This is the second constructor for the Reports class. This method is used for both the location report and the contacts report.
        Parameters:
        type - name of the type of appointment
        customerID - id of customer for that appointment
        contactID - id of the contact for that appointment
        start - date and time the appointment will start
        location - name of the location the appointment is at
        description - description of the appointment
        appointmentID - id of the appointment
        end - date and time the appointment will end
        title - title for the appointment
